    "rich_text_LGDmdF": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_en8FFq": {
          "type": "heading",
          "name": "GST on Diamond-Studded Jewellery",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "GST on Diamond-Studded Jewellery",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "text_q7c6Nk": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>GST on diamonds and diamond-studded pieces are calculated a little differently from gold and its different purities. This frequently causes confusion for a lot of shoppers, so let’s deep-dive and understand the nitty-gritties of how GST works in the world of diamonds:</p><ul><li>GST on loose cut and polished diamonds stands at 1.5% as of 2025.</li><li>However, once you set these diamonds into the jewellery, they are taxed at a combined value at 3%, and an additional 3% on the making charges. </li></ul><p>Let’s simplify this using an example. Let’s say you bought a piece worth ₹1,00,000 worth of gold, ₹25,000 worth of diamonds, and ₹10,000 in making charges. </p>"
          }
        }
      },
